# Getting Started with Node.js

Node.js allows you to run JavaScript on the server. It's fast, efficient, and has a massive ecosystem.

## Installation

Download Node.js from [nodejs.org](https://nodejs.org) and install it on your machine.

## Your First Server

```javascript
const http = require('http');

const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {
  res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'text/plain' });
  res.end('Hello World!');
});

server.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log('Server running on port 3000');
});
```

## Why Node.js?

1. **Non-blocking I/O** - Handles many connections simultaneously
2. **NPM Ecosystem** - Millions of packages available
3. **Same language** - JavaScript on both frontend and backend

Happy coding!
